folder: Pier 58 of the French Lines., Hudson River, Manhattan, NY
title: North (Hudson) River - Pier 58 of the French Lines.

text:
Eleventh Avenue, east side, from 17th to 18th Streets. April 2, 1929.
P.L. Sperr, Photographer.

(1)
North (Hudson) River, north from West 17th to West 22nd (left) Streets, showing piers 59, 60 and 61, off Eleventh Ave. In the center of the view is visible the Empire State Building under construction.
October 1, 1930.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
Another view, and including pier 58 (right). The S.S. Leviathan is docked at pier 59.
April 8, 1933.

P. L. Sperr.
title: North (Hudson) River - Shore and skyline - Manhattan - [Midtown skyline between 14th and 59th Streets - Empire State Building - Piers 58, 59, 60 and 61 ; S. S. Leviathan.]

folder: Piers 91, 92, and 93 - Manhattan., Hudson River, Manhattan, NY
text:
North (Hudson) River; showing Piers No. 91 and 92 (under construction and 93 (on the extreme right). In the foreground, the City is building several new 1000 foot structures to berth huge Trans-Atlantic liners. The photographer is viewing northward from W. 51st Street, to show the deep excavation necessitated by same. In the background, across the river is the Jersey Shore and highlands.

Oct. 3, 1933.
Views 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr,
title: North (Hudson) River - Piers 91, 92, and 93 - Manhattan.

folder: Piers 91, 92, and 93 - Manhattan., Hudson River, Manhattan, NY
text:
North (Hudson) River: showing Piers No. 91 and 92 (under construction) and 93 (right, covered in). These new structures will be 1000 feet long, enabling the huge ocean liners to berth have comfortably. The deep excavation necessitated by same is to the left where the steel towers stand. In the background, across the river, is the New Jersey Shore line. The photographer is viewing westward from a point between West 51st and 52nd Streets.

Oct. 3, 1933
Views 1 and 2

P. L. Sperr
title: North (Hudson) River - Piers 91, 92, and 93 - Manhattan.
